{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b356e07b-42ca-496d-8e54-2515804fc842","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the TFM:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet --version` to confirm the SDK, then `dotnet build` and `dotnet test` to catch any breaking changes. Also review the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any API or behavioral changes that may affect your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d5302129-b165-4d45-898f-dc6f7e158fe9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've already told me exactly what needs to change.","outputTokens":301,"requestId":"400D:3B722C:17569FC:1A384E5:69F94AD9"},"id":"c897f22e-95d6-477f-a370-c52d91a9310e","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:41:51.955Z","parentId":"911f5ebe-201b-4f3c-a476-168910b3823c"}
